      "\n  have h1 : Tendsto (fun k : ℝ => k * Real.sin (r / k)) atTop (𝓝 r) := by\n    have h2 : Tendsto (fun k : ℝ => (r / k) ) atTop (𝓝 0) := by\n      apply Tendsto.div_const\n      exact atTop_nhds\n      all_goals norm_num\n    have h3 : Tendsto (fun k : ℝ => Real.sin (r / k) / (r / k)) atTop (𝓝 (1 : ℝ)) := by\n      apply Real.tendsto_sin_div\n    have h4 : Tendsto (fun k : ℝ => k * Real.sin (r / k)) atTop (𝓝 r) := by\n      have h5 : (fun k : ℝ => k * Real.sin (r / k)) = fun k : ℝ => r * (Real.sin (r / k) / (r / k)) := by\n        funext k\n        field_simp\n        <;> ring\n      rw [h5]\n      apply Tendsto.mul_const\n      exact h3\n    exact h4\n  exact h1",
      "making `k` large enough.\n`| - (r/k)^2 / 6 + ... | < ε`.\nThis is `|(r/k)^2 / 6 - ...| < ε`.\n\nWe can make `(r/k)^2 / 6 < δ` by making `k` large enough.\nLet's solve for `k`: `(r/k)^2 / 6 < δ` => `r^2 / k^2 < 6δ` => `k^2 > r^2 / (6δ)` => `k > sqrt(r^2 / (6δ))`.\nSo, if we take `k > sqrt(r^2 / (6δ))`, then `(r/k)^2 / 6 < δ`.\n\nWe also need to bound the higher order terms. The Taylor expansion is `sin(x) = x - x^3/6 + x^5/120 - ...`.\nThe error after the quadratic term is `O(x^3)`.\nSo, `|Real.sin(r/k) - (r/k + (r/k)^3 / 6)| < ε`.\nWe need to make `(r/k)^3 / 6 < δ`.\nLet's solve for `k`: `(r/k)^3 / 6 < δ` => `r^3 / k^3 < 6δ` => `k^3 > r^3 / (6δ)` => `k > (r^3 / (6δ))^(1/3)`.\nSo, if we take `k > (r^3 / (6δ))^(1/3)`, then `(r/k)^3 / 6 < δ`.\n\nTo make both bounds work, we need `k > max(sqrt(r^2 / (6δ)), (r^3 / (6δ))^(1/3))`.\nLet's take `δ = ε / 2`.\nThen, `k > max(sqrt(r^2 / (6 * ε / 2)), (r^3 / (6 * ε / 2))^(1/3))`.\nSimplify: `k > max(sqrt(r^2 / (3 * ε)), (r^3 / (3 * ε))^(1/3))`.\nLet's take `δ = ε`.\nThen, `k > max(sqrt(r^2 / (6 * ε)), (r^3 / (6 * ε))^(1/3))`.\nLet's set `δ = ε / 2`.\nThen `k > max(sqrt(r^2 / (6 * (ε / 2))), (r^3 / (6 * (ε / 2)))^(1/3))`.\nSimplify: `k > max(sqrt(r^2 / (3 * ε)), (r^3 / (3 * ε))^(1/3))`.\n\nSo, we can take `K = { k | k ≥ sqrt(r^2 / (3 * ε)) + 1 } ∪ { k | k ≥ (r^3 / (3 * ε))^(1/3) + 1 }`.\nBut this is not compact in `ℝ`.\n\nWe need a compact set. So we have to take a finite interval.\nLet's think. We need `k` large enough. Let's take `K = [A, ∞)`.\nWe need `A` such that for all `k ≥ A`, `|k * Real.sin(r / k) - r| < ε`.\n\nWe can take `A = max(sqrt(r^2 / (3 * ε)), (r^3 / (3 * ε))^(1/3)) + 1`.\nBut this is not necessarily compact.\n\nWait, in the definition of `Tendsto`, the set `K` must be compact.\nSo we have to take a finite interval.\n\nLet's use the fact that `sin(x) = x - x^3/6 + x^5/120 - ...`.\nSo, `Real.sin(r / k) = r/k - (r/k)^3/6 + (r/k)^5/120 - ...`.\nThen `k * Real.sin(r / k) = k * (r/k - (r/k)^3/6 + (r/k)^5/120 -